    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - DISASSEMBLY - COUNTERSHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">This view (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022b8">Figure 118</hotlnk>) of the countershaft shows the direction of the gears. The
                gears are secured with three keys.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022b8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022b8" filename="../figg13/G13022b8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 118. Countershaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If a straight edge is placed between the teeth (painted here to show the timing marks),
                every gear on the countershaft will be in line with the blind spline on the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022b9">Figure 119</hotlnk>). When the shafts are in time, these marks will be
                directly across from each other. If they are out of alignment, check for worn or damaged keys or a
                twisted shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022b9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022b9" filename="../figg13/G13022b9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 119. Timing Marks</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
